body: Will "cond" potentially be a multi-dimensional tensor containing a single value? If yes, then the above solution isn't general enough to handle this.

No. There is only one condition variable used to decide if the 'then' or 'else' branch of the If is executed, so it can either be a value with no dims (shape == []) or a 1D tensor with one element (shape == []).

There's a helper that can handle an ndarray with a single value though - even if that shouldn't be possible in a valid model. the `if cond > 0:` in the original code could simply be replaced with `if as_scalar(cond) > 0:` with no other changes.

issue.title: Use 'as_scalar' when checking the 'cond' value of 'If'
